article.headline: Lafayette 57, Cornell 43
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- It was a career night for Drake's Chaun Brooks. The senior guard posted career highs in points (26) and steals (five) as the Bulldogs cruised to a 102-62 win Wednesday night over Cornell College. Drake (4-1) matched its best start since 1999-2000. Brooks, whose previous best was 16 points against Akron last year, had 15 points by halftime as Drake held an eight-point lead. The Bulldogs started the second half with a 19-2 burst behind three layups by Brooks, and took a 63-38 lead on a finger-roll layup by Al Stewart. Cornell (0-3), a Division III school, never mounted a serious threat while committing a season-high 31 turnovers. Drake turned the ball over 15 times. The Bulldogs went over the century mark for the first time since scoring 162 points against Grinnell three years ago. Jeff Ecker led the Rams with 22 points, including two early 3-pointers that gave Cornell an early 13-9 lead. The Bulldogs recovered with a 14-0 run midway through the first half to take a 27-19 lead with 6:44 left. Nick Grant finished with 13 points and Brent Heemskerk and Ajay Calvin collected 11 apiece for Drake. Drake plays Iowa State on Monday.
